```java
catch (org.mockito.exceptions.verification.junit.ArgumentsAreDifferent e) {
    error = handleVerifyException(e);
}
```

This is causing Mockito to have an implicit dependency on JUnit classes, which violates the principle that pure Mockito API should not depend on JUnit. The fix is to remove this specific catch block and handle the exception more generically.

