### Problem Analysis
The issue was in `src/org/mockito/internal/verification/VerificationOverTimeImpl.java` where there was a direct reference to the JUnit-specific exception class `org.mockito.exceptions.verification.junit.ArgumentsAreDifferent`. This created an unwanted dependency on JUnit libraries, which violated the constraint tested by `org.mockitointegration.NoJUnitDependenciesTest::pure_mockito_should_not_depend_JUnit`.

### Solution
I removed the specific catch block that directly referenced the JUnit-specific exception:

```java
// Removed this problematic catch block:
catch (org.mockito.exceptions.verification.junit.ArgumentsAreDifferent e) {
    error = handleVerifyException(e);
}
```

The JUnit-specific `ArgumentsAreDifferent` exception extends `MockitoAssertionError`, so it will now be caught by the existing general `catch (MockitoAssertionError e)` block, eliminating the direct dependency on JUnit while maintaining the same functionality.

